---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Navbar from "../components/Navbar.astro";
---

<Layout title="Valerio Clemenzi">
  <Navbar />

  <div class="mb-8 mt-24 text-center md:flex md:text-left">
    <div class="md:flex md:w-1/2 md:items-center md:justify-center">
      <div>
        <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold text-text">
          Hello, I'm <span class="underline">Valerio</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-2 text-lg text-gray-500">I am a young Italian developer</p>

        <div class="mt-4 flex">
          <a href="#about">
            <button
              class="mr-3 rounded-md bg-gyellow p-2 pl-7 pr-7 font-semibold text-text hover:underline"
            >
              Who am I?
            </button>
          </a>
          <a href="/skills">
            <button
              class="rounded-md bg-gpurple p-2 pl-7 pr-7 font-semibold text-text hover:underline"
            >
              What do I do?
            </button>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="hidden md:flex md:w-1/2 md:items-center md:justify-center">
      <img src="/favicon.ico" class="h-60 w-60 rounded-full border-8 border-ggreen" />
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr />

  <div id="about" class="m-5 rounded-md p-4 2xl:ml-96 2xl:mr-96">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-text">About Me!</h1>
    <p class="mt-3 text-lg text-text">
      Hello, I'm Valerio, and I'm a 14-year-old computer enthusiast. It all began when I first tried
      to create a bot for the Discord messaging platform, and it was love at first sight. So, from
      that day on, I started constantly learning new things: new programming languages, new habits,
      new goals. I quickly transitioned from Windows to Linux and replaced many of my software with
      open-source versions that respected my privacy. In no time, I learned JavaScript, then
      TypeScript, and explored new frameworks, and so on.
    </p>

    <p class="mt-3 text-lg text-text">
      Later on, I shifted from JavaScript, which had become my primary language for web development,
      to new languages that I'm still exploring and learning, such as Go and Rust, to specialize not
      only in web development but also in other areas
    </p>

    <p class="mt-3 text-lg text-text">
      In the future, I hope to learn new things like creating Android apps, artificial intelligence,
      and much more, turning this passion into a career, the job of my dreams.
    </p>

    <div class="inline-flex items-baseline">
      <h1 class="mt-2 text-gray-600">Not enough information? Contact me at:</h1>
      <a href="mailto:inbox@vclemenzi.dev" class="ml-1 text-gray-600 underline"
        >inbox@vclemenzi.dev</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <footer id="links" class="border-t-2">
    <div class="mb-4 mt-4 hidden md:flex md:justify-center">
      <a class="cursor-pointer hover:underline" href="https://github.com/vclemenzi"
        >github.com/vclemenzi</a
      >
      <span class="ml-1 mr-1 text-gray-500">|</span>
      <a class="cursor-pointer hover:underline" href="https://t.me/vclemenzi">t.me/vclemenzi</a>
      <span class="ml-1 mr-1 cursor-pointer text-gray-500">|</span>
      <a class="cursor-pointer hover:underline" href="https://matrix.to/#/@thebigbot:matrix.org"
        >@vclemenzi:matrix.org</a
      >
      <span class="ml-1 mr-1 text-gray-500">|</span>
      <a class="cursor-pointer hover:underline" href="mailto:inbox@vclemenzi.dev"
        >inbox@vclemenzi.dev</a
      >
    </div>
  </footer>
</Layout>
